videos.headline: Ashwin to Stoinis, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! Another catch in the deep for Jurel, and Royals are starting to take control of the game. Ashwin gets his first wicket. Carrom ball fired in full on leg stump, Stoinis slogs across the line, doesn't get enough on it and it's straight to deep midwicket. Stoinis c Dhruv Jurel b Ashwin 3(4)

Sandeep Sharma to Rahul, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! Sandeep Sharma, you beauty! Entrusted with the responsibility of bowling these critical overs, he's doing a stellar job so far, and has now delivered the big wicket of Rahul. Full and wide outside off, Rahul shuffles across to reach out and throws his bat at it. But he miscues it off the outside half and Jurel takes it safely at sweeper cover. Rahul c Dhruv Jurel b Sandeep Sharma 58(44) [4s-4 6s-2]

Chahal to Hooda, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! Steps out to Chahal first ball, and perishes. Didn't even have a look at him first before wanting to send him out of the park. It's pushed through at 98kph, Hooda is nowhere close to the pitch of it, goes through with the slog and drags it off the inside half to deep midwicket. Hooda c Dhruv Jurel b Chahal 26(13) [4s-2 6s-2]

Nandre Burger to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Buttler!! Burger has his first scalp in IPL 2024. The ball bowled at 147.2 clicks and Ayush Badoni looked to drive it on the up. The bat face turned a little on impact and he spooned an easy catch to the man at mid-off. Buttler won't drop those. Third one down for LSG and RR on top here. Ayush Badoni c Buttler b Nandre Burger 1(5)

Boult to Padikkal, out Bowled!! What happened there? The batter still reeling from the last ball? Was a length delivery, skidded on and Padikkal didn't move his feet and wanted to tuck it but missed the line to be clean bowled. The feet were stuck in cement and his first outing in LSG shirt has ended on a poor note. The perfume ball almost had him floored earlier and now the length delivery has done its job. He was stuck on the back foot. Second strike for Boult and RR are off to a superb start here. Padikkal b Boult 0(3)

Boult to de Kock, out Caught by Nandre Burger!! Boult would have taken many wickets with the new ball but has to be one of the luckiest for sure. Easy take for the Impact sub - Burger - who takes it with elan. Was a poor delivery on the pads, de Kock whipped it and found the hands of the man at long leg. A little to the left or right and it would have been a boundary but not to be. de Kock is distraught and has to walk off. de Kock c Nandre Burger b Boult 4(5) [4s-1]

Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, out Caught by Rahul!! Hetmyer didn't realize he nicked it. The onfield umpire also took his time signalling it out. But Hetmyer thought he hadn't edged it. But UltraEdge showed a little spike and Hetmyer has to go without disturbing the scorers much. Fourth one down for RR. They needed Hetmyer to play a good cameo but they have lost him and a review as well. Hetmyer c Rahul b Ravi Bishnoi 5(7)

Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, out Caught by (sub)Hooda!! One shot too many from Parag. He has to go now. That was a short ball, dug in, Riyan Parag went for the pull and got a top-edge. The balance wasn't there as he made contact. The ball went very high and the man from deep square came in, got under it and took it with elan. Hooda had no qualms. Huge wicket for LSG as Riyan Parag was taking the game away alongside his skipper. Riyan Parag c (sub)Hooda b Naveen-ul-Haq 43(29) [4s-1 6s-3]

Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, out Caught by Krunal Pandya!! That's a soft dismissal and RR have lost both openers now. Banged in short and just outside off - Jaiswal was shaping for the pull, the length wasn't short though, cramped him for room and rushed him for pace, lobs a simple catch to mid-on, coming high off the bat. Jaiswal was looking impressive, but his cameo has been cut short. Jaiswal c Krunal Pandya b Mohsin Khan 24(12) [4s-3 6s-1]

Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged and caught! That's a body blow for RR - fuller length delivery and in that channel just outside off,. Buttler went with hard hands on the drive, gets a thick edge and KL does the rest, moving swiftly to his right and pouching a tow-handed low catch - Buttler was looking aggressive, but he's sent packing early. Naveen-ul-Haq 11(9) [4s-2]
